assigned an BI-RADS Assessment Category using a 5-point scale\nbased on the likelihood that findings correlates with the presence of a clinically\nsignificant ovarian cancer\nTAKE HOME MASSAGES :\nBreast cancer\n• Screening is done for totally asymptomatic females (start above the age of 40 years\nbut earlier in high risk females)\n• The aim of screening is to detect breast lesions early before the female feels a lump\n• Screening is done using Mammography\n• Mammography is the best modality to detect calcifications of DCIS which is the\nearliest signs of malignancy.\n• Diagnostic mammography is done for patients with symptoms (i.e. those with a\nbreast lump, focal pain, nipple inversion, bloody nipple discharge).\n• US is complimentary to mammography to differentiate between cystic and\nsolid lesions and characterize a mass as benign or malignant\n• Contrast–enhanced breast MR imaging is used selectively to improve breast\ncancer staging (i.e. to detect multifocal tumours).\n• BI-RADS system (Breast imaging reporting and data system) = to stratify breast\nlesions = from benign to malignant spectrum\n• Abnormalities visible on US are biopsied under US guidance. If no abnormality is\nseen on US in a region of concern, a stereotactic biopsy can be performed, using\nmammographic images to localise the abnormality and guide the biopsy.\n116"}